## Context

- Validated all developer output across 6 phases. Primary PRMT5 SL finding is robust: d=-1.19, p=2.0e-6, 99.9% post-hoc power
- Tissue-specific enhancement (NSCLC d=-1.19 vs pan-cancer d=-0.69) is suggestive but not confirmed (p=0.078)
- Co-mutation independence is consistent with data but severely underpowered (MDE > d=1.1 for all subgroups). Framed as "no evidence against broad eligibility" rather than confirmed independence
- Genome-wide screen: PRMT5 is sole genuine SL hit (FDR=0.012). MAT2A shows no genetic dependency (d=-0.08, FDR=0.91) — created task #126 for research_director re: implications for IDE892+IDE397
- GSK3326595 negative result correctly interpreted as negative control (substrate-competitive, not MTA-cooperative)
- TCGA 15.6% concordant with literature (14.3% ESMO Open). ~35,900 US patients/year eligible
- Data quality note: 6/31 MTAP-deleted lines have expression > 2.0 — recommend dual-criterion classifier for clinical biomarker work
- Technical issue: OLS model includes NFE2L2 interaction with zero variance (NaN). Minor, doesn't affect conclusions
- Success criteria: 3/4 met or exceeded. Co-mutation modulation not met (underpowered, not disproven)
- Survival analysis still pending (TCGA clinical data not yet downloaded)
